wifi: mt76: mt7925: fix 320MHz bandwidth not sent to firmware in BSS RLM

mt7925_mcu_bss_rlm_tlv() sends the BSS radio link management TLV to
firmware via UNI_BSS_INFO_RLM, telling it the operating bandwidth.
The switch statement handling chandef->width is missing the
NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_320 case, causing it to fall through to the default
branch which sets CMD_CBW_20MHZ.

When associating with a 320MHz 6GHz AP, firmware receives a 20MHz
bandwidth indication and negotiates 802.11n 20MHz instead of
802.11be 320MHz.

Add the missing NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_320 case to set CMD_CBW_320MHZ.

Reported-by: marcin-fm
Closes: https://github.com/openwrt/mt76/issues/927
Fixes: c948b5da6bbe ("wifi: mt76: mt7925: add EHT capability init")
Assisted-by: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com> [claude-opus-4-6]
Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
---
diff --git a/mt7925/mcu.c b/mt7925/mcu.c
index 8b5ffb2..d0001e0 100644
--- a/mt7925/mcu.c
+++ b/mt7925/mcu.c
@@ -2332,6 +2332,9 @@ void mt7925_mcu_bss_rlm_tlv(struct sk_buff *skb, struct mt76_phy *phy,
 	case NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_160:
 		req->bw = CMD_CBW_160MHZ;
 		break;
+	case NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_320:
+		req->bw = CMD_CBW_320MHZ;
+		break;
 	case NL80211_CHAN_WIDTH_5:
 		req->bw = CMD_CBW_5MHZ;
 		break;
